/open_telemetry/v3/logs_service.proto\n\n**7. Wasm Access Logger (envoy.access_loggers.wasm)**\n- **Location**: source/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/ (config.cc, config.h, wasm_access_log_impl.h)\n- **JSON Support**: DEPENDS ON WASM MODULE\n- **Details**: Delegates all logging logic to WebAssembly modules. The format (JSON or otherwise) depends entirely on the wasm module's implementation. The proto defines WasmAccessLog which takes PluginConfig for loading the wasm module.\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/v3/wasm.proto\n\n**8. Dynamic Modules Access Logger (envoy.access_loggers.dynamic_modules)**\n- **JSON Support**: DEPENDS ON DYNAMIC MODULE\n- **Details**: Similar to wasm, delegates logging to dynamically loaded shared objects. Format depends on module implementation. The proto shows DynamicModuleAccessLog with logger_config (google.protobuf.Any) and logger_name for module identification.\n- **Proto Only**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/dynamic_modules/v3/dynamic_modules.proto (no C++ implementation in v1.31.2)\n\n**9. Stats Access Logger (envoy.access_loggers.stats)**\n- **JSON Support**: N/A - NOT A LOG SINK\n- **Details**: This is a metrics/statistics emitter, not a log sink. It emits counters and histograms based on access log data. Does not produce logs in any format.\n- **Proto Only**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stats/v3/stats.proto (no C++ implementation in v1.31.2)\n\n### Access Log Filter Implementations\n\nThese are not sinks but filters that control WHICH logs get written:\n\n**1. CEL Access Log Filter (envoy.access_loggers.extension_filters.cel)**\n- **Location**: source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/ (config.cc, config.h, cel.h)\n- **Type**: FILTER (not sink)\n- **Details**: Uses Common Expression Language to evaluate expressions for filtering access log emission. The filter evaluates expressions against stream attributes and returns boolean result.\n- **Proto**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/v3/cel.proto\n\n**2. Process RateLimit Filter (envoy.access_loggers.extension_filters.process_ratelimit)**\n- **Type**: FILTER (not sink)\n- **Details**: Rate limits access log emission using token bucket algorithm. Protobuf-only in this version.\n- **Proto Only**: envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/process_ratelimit/v3/process_ratelimit.proto\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Logger | Type | JSON Support | C++ Implementation | Proto Definition |\n|--------|------|--------------|-------------------|------------------|\n| File | Sink | YES | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/file/v3/file.proto |\n| Stdout | Sink | YES | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stream/v3/stream.proto |\n| Stderr | Sink | YES | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stream/v3/stream.proto |\n| Fluentd | Sink | YES | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/v3/fluentd.proto |\n| HTTP gRPC | Sink | YES* | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto |\n| TCP gRPC | Sink | YES* | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto |\n| OpenTelemetry | Sink | YES | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/v3/logs_service.proto |\n| Wasm | Sink | DEPENDS | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/v3/wasm.proto |\n| Dynamic Modules | Sink | DEPENDS | NO | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/dynamic_modules/v3/dynamic_modules.proto |\n| Stats | Metrics | N/A | NO | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stats/v3/stats.proto |\n| CEL | Filter | N/A | YES | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/v3/cel.proto |\n| Process RateLimit | Filter | N/A | NO | envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/process_ratelimit/v3/process_ratelimit.proto |\n\n*gRPC loggers use protobuf messages which are inherently structured and can be serialized as JSON.\n\n### Key Findings\n\n1. **Nine structured logging implementations** support JSON format explicitly or implicitly:\n   - Seven sink implementations: File, Stream (2x), Fluentd, gRPC (2x), OpenTelemetry\n   - Two extensible implementations: Wasm 